rows.label: qev060609_MSG0001
rows.name:
*fsssh* Have you spoken with Orleron,
the newest member of our mission?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0002
rows.name:
Arsenican has coughed forth a fine addition to our
ranks, all by the grace of devoltanization. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0003
rows.name:
I...suppose you saw that argument. *fsssh*
How embarrassing.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0004
rows.name:
How could he have grown up to be such a...
To be as he is? *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0005
rows.name:
Perhaps New LA is not as suitable an environment for
us Zaruboggan as we had thought. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_SEL0011
rows.name: Nod and say that Trachlo may be right.

rows.label: qev060609_SEL0021
rows.name: Protest that what Trachlo says isn't the case.

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0006
rows.name:
*fsssh* Ah. To hear a human say it makes it all the
more convincing.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0007
rows.name:
Perhaps we must explore a method of raising our
young in a place far from human influence. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0008
rows.name:
You are probably right. *fsssh* After all, the rest of us
happily cohabitate with you with no ill effect.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0009
rows.name:
Perhaps just a small adjustment to the way our young
are exposed to human influence will ensure that tragic
cases like Orleron do not occur again. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0010
rows.name:
*fsssh* Orleron has grown into a proud and reliable
Zaruboggan.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0011
rows.name:
He follows the path laid out for us by Golbogga on the
Day of Regrowth. *fsssh* He follows straight and true.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev060609_MSG0012
rows.name: In time, I hope he may succeed me. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]
